LXC
--------------
lxc-ls to list containers,
lxc-info to obtain detailed container information, 
lxc-start to start and 
lxc-stop to stop the container. 
lxc-attach and lxc-console allow you to enter a container, if ssh is not an option. 
lxc-destroy removes the container, including its rootfs. See the manual pages for more information on each command. An example session might look like:


sudo lxc-ls --fancy
sudo lxc-start --name u1 --daemon
sudo lxc-info --name u1
sudo lxc-stop --name u1
sudo lxc-destroy --name u1